technology.p:
You can use your graphing calculator to solve the problem in . Graph the two equations

	\begin{align}
	Y_1 \amp= 256X - 16X^2\\
	Y_2 \amp= 800
	\end{align}

on the same screen. Use WINDOW settings to match the graph in . Then use the intersect feature to find the x-coordinates of the points where the two graphs intersect (there are two of them). These points will have y-coordinates of 800. The parabola is above the line, so h \gt 800 when t is between these two x-values. To two decimal places, you can see that h \gt 800 when 4.26 \lt t \lt 11.74.

